Pre-Game Insights: New Zealand have beaten South Africa six times in eight meetings.
South Africa are among the biggest batting teams at the tournament.
New Zealand are themselves not averse to piling on the runs.
Lockie Ferguson, Kane Williamson, and Mark Chapman are carrying significant injuries.
The match is more about who goes where in the final four than anything else.
Both teams will be reasonably confident of making the semis, but will they play Australia or India there?
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is between New Zealand and South Africa in the ICC Cricket World Cup 2023.
The match will be played at the Maharashtra Cricket Association Stadium, Pune on November 1, 2023.
The match is a crucial one for both teams as it will help them determine their position in the final four.
The teams have a history of producing exciting matches, with New Zealand having beaten South Africa six times in eight meetings.
The match will be a test of both teams' batting and bowling abilities.
Others: Kagiso Rabada missed the match against Pakistan in Chennai on Friday because of lower back spasms, but should be good to go on Wednesday.
South Africa's only other question is whether to pick Tabraiz Shamsi as a second spinner rather than Gerald Coetzee, their fast bowling enforcer.

New Zealand's probable XI includes Devon Conway, Will Young, Rachin Ravindra, Daryl Mitchell, Tom Latham, Glenn Phillips, Jimmy Neesham, Mitchell Santner, Matt Henry, Trent Boult, and Lockie Ferguson.

South Africa's probable XI includes Temba Bavuma, Quinton de Kock, Rassie van der Dussen, Aiden Markram, Heinrich Klaasen, David Miller, Marco Jansen, Kagiso Rabada, Keshav Maharaj, Gerald Coetzee, and Lungi Ngidi.
